Racial diversity scores are measured in terms of the six racial and ethnic groups—namely White, Black, Asian,  Pacific Islander, American Indian and Alaska Native,  Hispanic, and other race or two or more races -- assessing the number of different groups in each state and the size of each group.  The minimum score, 0, indicates  only one racial or ethnic group  in the state.  Source: Table 1, Shaw, Elyse, and Emma Williams-Baron. "Women of Color: Where They Are in the United States."
